headline: How AI will drive profit growth for credit cards, retailers in 2026

headline: Target (TGT): Has the Recent 14% Rebound Uncovered a Mispriced Recovery Story?
summary: Target (TGT) has quietly staged a comeback, with shares gaining about 14% over the past month, even as the stock remains roughly 29% lower year to date. See our latest analysis for Target. That 13.9% 30 day share price return looks more like a sentiment reset than a blip, especially given year to date share price losses and still negative five year total shareholder returns. This suggests a longer term turnaround story is only just being tested. If Target’s rebound has you thinking about what...
